Memory is organized into byte-sized units.
Each unit has a unique address.
However, most variables take more than one byte.   

Size of C++ basic types

#boolean
bool            | 1 byte

# characters
char            | 1 byte
wchar_t         | 1 byte
char16_t        | 2 byte
char32_t        | 4 byte


# integers
short           | 2 byte
int             | 2 byte
long            | 4 byte
long long       | 8 byte


# floating point
float           | 4 byte
double          | 8 byte
long double     | 8 byte

# size_of
